max_steps: Max steps reached - Vision analysis: This shows the Instagram "New reel" creation screen where a user is in the final step of posting a reel. The screen displays the reel preview (a car in a parking garage with "POV: You comeback to your hometown after u made it" text), along with options to add caption, hashtags, tag people, add location, and other posting settings.

The post likely failed to complete because the user reached the maximum number of steps (30) in the posting flow without actually hitting the "Share" button, which is clearly visible at the bottom right. To fix this, the user simply needs to click the blue "Share" button to publish the reel.
